The Taco Liberty Bell was an April Fool's Day joke played by Fast-food restaurant|fast food restaurant chain Taco Bell. On April 1, 1996, Taco Bell took out a full-page advertisement in ''The New York Times'' announcing that they had purchased the Liberty Bell to &quot;reduce the country's debt&quot; and renamed it the &quot;Taco Liberty Bell&quot;. Thousands of people protested before it was revealed to them that the sale was a hoax.

Press secretary Mike McCurry responded that the federal government was also &quot;selling the Lincoln Memorial to Ford Motor Co. and renaming it the Lincoln-Mercury Memorial.&quot;;;

